Hungary’s OTP in Talks to Purchase RBS’s Romanian Unit, ZF Says

-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 
2011-05-02T06:44:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/hungary-s-otp-in-talks-to-purchase-rbs-s-romanian-unit-zf-says.html
OTP Bank Nyrt.,  Hungary ’s largest
lender, is in talks with  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS)  about
the purchase of the British bank’s Romanian unit, Ziarul
Financiar reported, citing unidentified people.  OTP will file a preliminary offer for the Romanian unit of
Britain’s biggest government-controlled bank in about two weeks,
the Bucharest-based newspaper said, citing the unidentified
people.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  